---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Protocol Docs"
  description="Open GeoFeed Protocol specification — SubdivisionPath, GeoFeeds, registry architecture, and API reference."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 pt-16 pb-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs text-emerald-400 mb-4 tracking-widest uppercase">
        Documentation
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white mb-4">
        Open GeoFeed Protocol
      </h1>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-12 text-lg">
        Protocol specification, registry architecture, and API reference.
      </p>

      <!-- Core Concepts -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-800">
          Core Concepts
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-8">

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-mono text-sm text-emerald-400 mb-2">SubdivisionPath</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-3">
              A slash-separated sequence of lowercase slugs starting with an ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 country code.
              Paths are hierarchical and unambiguous — each segment narrows the geographic scope.
            </p>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900 p-4 font-mono text-sm">
              <div class="space-y-1 text-neutral-400">
                <div><span class="text-emerald-400">bra</span><span class="text-neutral-600 ml-4"># country</span></div>
                <div><span class="text-emerald-400">bra/sp</span><span class="text-neutral-600 ml-4"># state</span></div>
                <div><span class="text-emerald-400">bra/sp/sao-paulo</span><span class="text-neutral-600 ml-4"># municipality</span></div>
                <div><span class="text-emerald-400">bra/sp/sao-paulo/tatuape</span><span class="text-neutral-600 ml-4"># neighborhood</span></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-mono text-sm text-emerald-400 mb-2">GeoFeeds</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-3">
              Activity feeds in Actor-Verb-Object format (ActivityPub wire format), anchored to a geopath.
              Any actor — business, person, government — can publish a feed for any geopath they operate in.
            </p>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900 p-4 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-400">
              user:gi-matos → place:salao → subdivision:bra/sp/sao-paulo/tatuape
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <h3 class="font-mono text-sm text-emerald-400 mb-2">Registry</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
              The registry operates like DNS root servers: it knows what geopaths exist and which
              servers are authoritative for them, but delegates actual content to registered servers.
              Anyone can register as a content server without permission from the registry operator.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- API Reference -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-800">
          API Reference
        </h2>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          {[
            {
              method: "GET",
              path: "api.geofeed.ai/{geopath}",
              description: "Returns registry metadata for a geopath: name, type, parent, registered servers, and geometry.",
            },
            {
              method: "GET",
              path: "api.geofeed.ai/{geopath}/children",
              description: "Lists direct children of a geopath (e.g., all neighborhoods in a municipality).",
            },
            {
              method: "GET",
              path: "md.geofeed.ai/{geopath}",
              description: "Returns the same metadata as a Markdown document — optimized for LLM consumption and RAG pipelines.",
            },
            {
              method: "GET",
              path: "mcp.geofeed.ai",
              description: "MCP server endpoint. Provides resolve_geopath and list_children tools for AI agents.",
            },
          ].map((endpoint) => (
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-800 p-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2 font-mono text-sm">
                <span class="text-xs bg-emerald-900 text-emerald-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">{endpoint.method}</span>
                <span class="text-neutral-300">{endpoint.path}</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">{endpoint.description}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- SubdivisionType levels -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-800">
          SubdivisionType Levels
        </h2>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-neutral-800 overflow-hidden">
          <table class="w-full text-sm font-mono">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-neutral-800 bg-neutral-900">
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-neutral-500 font-normal">local_level</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-neutral-500 font-normal">type_slug</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-neutral-500 font-normal">name (Brazil)</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-800">
              {[
                [1, "bra", "Country"],
                [2, "bra-state", "Estado"],
                [3, "bra-municipality", "Município"],
                [4, "bra-district", "Distrito"],
                [5, "bra-subdistrict", "Subdistrito"],
                [6, "bra-neighborhood", "Bairro"],
              ].map(([level, slug, name]) => (
                <tr class="hover:bg-neutral-900 transition-colors">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-400">{level}</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-emerald-400">{slug}</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-400">{name}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Server types -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-800">
          Server Types
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          {[
            { type: "index", description: "Static presence — name, address, contact. No activity feed." },
            { type: "feed", description: "Activity feed — posts, events, offers anchored to the geopath." },
            { type: "signal", description: "Real-time feed — high-frequency updates, sensor data, live events." },
            { type: "promoted:true", description: "Promoted placement — shown above organic results (Findera Ads)." },
          ].map((s) => (
            <div class="flex gap-4 items-start rounded-lg border border-neutral-800 p-4">
              <span class="font-mono text-emerald-400 text-xs mt-0.5 shrink-0">{s.type}</span>
              <p class="text-neutral-400">{s.description}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- llms.txt -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-800">
          LLM Integration
        </h2>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-4">
          geofeed.ai ships an <code class="font-mono text-emerald-400">/llms.txt</code> at the root — a machine-readable
          index of the protocol for LLM crawlers and RAG systems.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
          All pages include JSON-LD structured data (Schema.org). The <code class="font-mono text-emerald-400">md.</code> subdomain
          serves every geopath as plain Markdown for direct LLM ingestion.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
